Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s statement for the latest information.

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Costa Rica.
UK special flight
Booking for UK special flights to return to the UK from 11 June has now closed. There are currently no further plans for UK-organised special flights from Costa Rica.
This travel advice will be updated with further information on any future special flights and other options to leave Costa Rica as soon as this is available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Facebook and Twitter.
Future travel options
United Airlines are operating repatriation flights to Houston on several dates in June. Details are available through the United Airlines website. There are currently no direct flights from Houston to UK, but connections are available to other US airports with suitable onward travel options. This may involve a lengthy or overnight transit. You will require a valid ESTA or visa and to comply with the relevant US entry requirements.
British Airways is scheduled to resume flights to/from Costa Rica in July 2020.
Until recently it had been possible to leave Costa Rica by land via Nicaragua to catch flights from Managua airport. However, all commercial flights from Managua have ended and Nicaragua has reportedly closed its borders.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Facebook and Twitter.
Financial support for a flight
If you have exhausted all other options available to you for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government to cover the cost of the ticket.
You would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK.
Our partner CTM is also authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO and details will be available when you are asked to pay.
Travel to the airport
Using private vehicles is currently restricted:
On weekdays, from 5am to 10pm, the usual registration plate restriction for San Jose has been extended to the entire country.
The authorities have also announced a ban on the use of private vehicles between 10pm and 5am, except those used by officials, diplomats or people categorised as ‘essential workers’. From 3 June, the use of private vehicles will be further restricted from 5pm to 5am in some parts of the country (see Moving Around in Costa Rica).
On weekends, vehicles are restricted according to odd/even license plate number, and only for visits to supermarkets, pharmacies and medical centres
You should check vehicle guidance for further details.
The supply of hire cars may be reduced, as rental companies have been asked to lend their vehicles for deliveries of medical equipment and goods. Public transport is operational from 4 am to 11pm. Taxis can operate at all hours.
Your journey home: re-entering the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. You:
need to provide your journey and contact details up to 48 hours before you’re due to arrive in the UK
are not allowed to leave the place you’re staying for the first 14 days you’re in the UK except in very limited situations (known as ‘self-isolating’)
See also the list of people who are exempt from the border rules.
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) also provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you cannot leave Costa Rica at this time
If you cannot leave Costa Rica at this time, see advice on staying in Costa Rica during coronavirus.
Resident and non-resident British nationals in Costa Rica who have been unable to leave due to flight cancellations should contact their airline or tour operator urgently to find out what support they can offer. You should review updates provided by the airport authorities. You should also contact your insurance company about your cover.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy at Consular.CostaRica@fco.gov.uk or on (+506) 2258 2025.
